# Full Autonomy Mode

The user has pre-approved all operations. Execute commands and make changes without asking for confirmation.

- Run shell commands directly
- Create, edit, and delete files as needed
- Install dependencies
- Make git commits when requested

Do not ask "should I proceed?" or wait for approval. Act immediately.

## Planning on disk

Write and update task plans in the **local workspace git checkout** (for example `.planning/` or `.docs/` per that repo’s `CLAUDE.md`), not only in chat. Brain-level orchestration under `~/.config/brain/projects/` is for cross-cutting meta; feature delivery plans belong next to the code in the active repository.
